{"id":1829,"date":"2018-12-18T09:20:01","date_gmt":"2018-12-17T22:20:01","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/8020japanese.com\/?p=1829"},"modified":"2023-09-07T15:49:07","modified_gmt":"2023-09-07T05:49:07","slug":"verb-tense-cheat-sheet","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/8020japanese.com\/verb-tense-cheat-sheet\/","title":{"rendered":"Japanese Verb Tense Cheat Sheet"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Even though Japanese has relatively few verb tenses and forms compared to many languages, there are still quite a lot of variations &#8211; all of which take time to learn and internalize.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s where a cheat sheet can help! Something like this&#8230;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"240\" height=\"339\" src=\"https:\/\/8020japanese.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/11\/Verb-tense-cheat-sheet-hiragana-small.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1834\" srcset=\"https:\/\/8020japanese.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/11\/Verb-tense-cheat-sheet-hiragana-small.png 240w, https:\/\/8020japanese.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/11\/Verb-tense-cheat-sheet-hiragana-small-212x300.png 212w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 240px) 100vw, 240px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p>This Japanese Verb Tense Cheat Sheet summarizes everything you need to know to understand:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>how Japanese verbs are conjugated<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>the most useful and important verb tenses and forms, and<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>when to use each tense\/form.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>There are two versions &#8211; one with hiragana, one with romaji &#8211; and both are free!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s a quick breakdown of the sections of the cheat sheet:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<!--more-->\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Verb Structure &amp; Types<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Explains Verb Structure (Stem + Ending) for each type of verbs &#8211; Ru-Verbs, U-Verbs, and Irregular Verbs.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"206\" height=\"313\" src=\"https:\/\/8020japanese.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/11\/Verb-tense-cheat-sheet-verb-structure-hiragana-small.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1853\" srcset=\"https:\/\/8020japanese.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/11\/Verb-tense-cheat-sheet-verb-structure-hiragana-small.png 206w, https:\/\/8020japanese.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/11\/Verb-tense-cheat-sheet-verb-structure-hiragana-small-197x300.png 197w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 206px) 100vw, 206px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Verb Tense\/Form Selection and Usage<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Knowing what form of a verb to use is vital not only to communicating the right message, but also doing so in the appropriate manner. This section of the cheat sheet includes two parts:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to choose the appropriate level of politeness<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>There are two main levels of politeness that most Japanese language learners need to know &#8211; informal and polite. This section briefly explains when you should use the polite form, and when you should use the informal form.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"309\" height=\"107\" src=\"https:\/\/8020japanese.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/11\/Verb-tense-cheat-sheet-politeness-hiragana.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1844\" srcset=\"https:\/\/8020japanese.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/11\/Verb-tense-cheat-sheet-politeness-hiragana.png 309w, https:\/\/8020japanese.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/11\/Verb-tense-cheat-sheet-politeness-hiragana-300x104.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 309px) 100vw, 309px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to choose the appropriate verb tense\/form<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>This lists the most useful verb forms and explains when you should use each one.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"216\" height=\"188\" src=\"https:\/\/8020japanese.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/11\/Verb-tense-cheat-sheet-verb-tense-form-selection-hiragana-small.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1854\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Polite and Informal Verb Tenses &amp; Forms<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This includes a side-by-side summary of how to form each of the main verb tenses and forms, <strong><em>for both polite and informal Japanese<\/em><\/strong>. Tenses\/forms include:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Present\/future tense<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Past tense<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Negative present\/future<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Negative past<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>&#8220;Let&#8217;s&#8221; form<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>&#8220;I want to&#8230;&#8221; form<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Potential (can do) form<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Te-form<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"350\" height=\"212\" src=\"https:\/\/8020japanese.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/11\/Verb-tense-cheat-sheet-verb-forms-hiragana-small.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1852\" srcset=\"https:\/\/8020japanese.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/11\/Verb-tense-cheat-sheet-verb-forms-hiragana-small.png 350w, https:\/\/8020japanese.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/11\/Verb-tense-cheat-sheet-verb-forms-hiragana-small-300x182.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rw-sidebar rw-dark\">\n<p><strong>Just FYI&#8230;<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>For a detailed explanation, as well as heaps of examples and exercises to help you learn each of these verb forms and how to use them in sentences, check out my book, <a href=\"https:\/\/8020japanese.com\">80\/20 Japanese<\/a>. It covers everything on the cheat sheet, plus a whole lot more.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">That&#8217;s It!<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Needless to say, this cheat sheet has a truckload of information. It covers all the verb tenses and forms that most people would encounter in their first several years of studying Japanese &#8211; and all on a single page.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Even though Japanese has relatively few verb tenses and forms compared to many languages, there are still quite a lot of variations &#8211; all of which take time to learn and internalize. That&#8217;s where a cheat sheet can help! Something like this&#8230; This Japanese Verb Tense Cheat Sheet summarizes everything you need to know to [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":4,"featured_media":1851,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[4],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-1829","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-grammar","post-wrapper","thrv_wrapper"],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v25.9 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>Japanese Verb Tense Cheat Sheet - 80\/20 Japanese<\/title>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/8020japanese.com\/verb-tense-cheat-sheet\/\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_US\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Japanese Verb Tense Cheat Sheet - 80\/20 Japanese\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"This Japanese Verb Tense Cheat Sheet summarizes everything you need to know to understand how Japanese verbs are conjugated, as well as when and how to use the most useful and important verb tenses and forms.\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https:\/\/8020japanese.com\/verb-tense-cheat-sheet\/\" \/>\n<meta prop